  "text": "The 'dependent variable' was self-rated health. Self-rated health is well established as an indicator of morbidity [CITATION_1] and a predictor of mortality. [CITATION_2] It was measured by the answer to the question, 'In general, is your health. . .?' on a 5-point scale ranging from 'very bad' to 'very good'. Consistent with previous research on neighbourhood social capital and health, the variable was dichotomized because its distribution is highly skewed (80.1% had good or very good health).",
